                  <handDesc>
                     <!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>The following names are mentioned in the
                        supplication formulas (inserted in the main hand): Gabra Dǝngǝl and Walatta
                        Krǝstos (<locus target="#10vb">10vb</locus>, 11rb, 13ra etc.), Za-Walda
                        Māryām and Walatta Ṣādǝqān (<locus target="#18va">18va</locus>, 31rb etc.),
                        Takla Yoḥannǝs and ʿAmda Māryām (<locus target="#28ra">28ra</locus>, 35ra
                           etc.).<date>19th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the protagonist and of the
                           angel Gabrǝʾel (fols. 89rb, 99va-100ra, 107rb, 107vb, 109rb); names of
                           the donors; words addressing the reader on fols. 11rb, 22ra; elements of
                           the punctuation signs and of the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.&#xD; &#xD; Several groups of lines on the incipit page of Text
                           I (alternating with black lines); two or three initial lines in the
                           incipit of sections (homilies), sometimes alternating with black lines
                           (e.g., fols. 61rb, 89ra, 97vb); one or two initial lines of subsections
                           (miracles and commemorative notices); the first word in the incipit of
                           subsections (hymns), i.e. salām "salutation".</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
